{{Infobox website | name = BuggedPlanet | logo = | logo_size = 160px | logo_alt = | logo_caption = <!-- or: | logocaption = --> | screenshot = | collapsible = <!-- set as "on", "y", etc, otherwise omit/leave blank --> | collapsetext = <!-- collapsible area's heading (default "Screenshot"); omit/leave blank if collapsible not set --> | background = <!-- for collapsetext heading; default grey (gainsboro) --> | screenshot_size = <!-- default 300px --> | screenshot_alt = | caption = | url = {{URL|http://www.BuggedPlanet.info}} | slogan = | commercial = No | type = | registration = | language = [[English language|English]] | num_users = | content_license = <!-- or: | content_licence = --> | programming_language = | owner = <!-- Andy Müller-Maguhn --> | author = [[Andy Müller-Maguhn]] | editor = <!-- or: | editors = --> | launch_date = 2011<!-- {{start date and age|YYYY|MM|DD|df=yes/no}} --> | revenue = | alexa = <!-- {{increase}} {{steady}} {{decrease}} [http://www.alexa.com/siteinfo/example.com ##] (US/Global MM/YYYY) --> | ip = | current_status = Online | footnotes = }} '''BuggedPlanet.info''' is a [[Wiki]] created in 2011<ref>{{cite web|last1=Greis|first1=Friedhelm|title=Ein warmes Mittagessen für den Staatstrojaner|url=http://www.golem.de/news/ueberwachungssoftware-ein-warmes-mittagessen-fuer-den-staatstrojaner-1407-108080.html|accessdate=31 May 2015|date=24 July 2014}}</ref> by [[Andy Müller-Maguhn]], former spokesman of the [[Chaos Computer Club]], that tries to list and track down the activities of the [[surveillance industry]] in the fields of "[[Lawful interception]]", [[Signals intelligence]] (SIGINT), [[Communications intelligence]] (COMINT) as well as tactical and strategical measures used to intercept communications and the vendors and governmental and private operators of this technology.<ref name="ccc">{{cite web|title=28th Chaos Communication Congress - BuggedPlanet|url=https://events.ccc.de/congress/2011/Fahrplan/events/4916.en.html|publisher=Chaos Computer Club|accessdate=31 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=BuggedPlanet - About|url=http://buggedplanet.info/index.php?title=Buggedplanet.info:About|website=BuggedPlanet.info|accessdate=31 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Klofta|first1=Jasmin|title=Die Achse des Guten|url=http://daserste.ndr.de/panorama/aktuell/gamma111.html|website=daserste.ndr.de|publisher=Das Erste|accessdate=31 May 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite book|last1=Ammann|first1=Thomas|last2=Aust|first2=Stefan|title=Digitale Diktatur: Totalüberwachung Cyberkrieg Datenmissbrauch|date=10 October 2014|publisher=Econ|isbn=978-3430201827|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=dXkXBAAAQBAJ&pg=PT132&dq=buggedplanet|accessdate=31 May 2015}}</ref><ref name=spiegel>{{cite web|last1=Horchert|first1=Judith|title=Überwachungssoftware: Hacker auf der dunklen Seite|url=http://www.spiegel.de/netzwelt/netzpolitik/spionage-software-hacker-berichtet-ueber-ausstieg-bei-dreamlab-a-921705.html|publisher=SPIEGEL Online|accessdate=31 May 2015|date=13 September 2013}}</ref>
The site maintains a list of vendors of [[cyberweapon]]s and <!--mass?-->[[surveillance technologies]] as well as a "country knowledgebase" that aims to accumulate country-specific news, activities and vendors on the topic. A special focus is placed on vendors that sell such technologies to undemocratic countries and related [[lobbying]] efforts.<ref name="ccc"/>
==The Spy Files== In December 2011 [[Privacy International]] and [[WikiLeaks]] collaborated with BuggedPlanet when they released documents collected from a number of surveillance trade shows and conferences included brochures, catalogues, technical specifications, contracts and pricelists for the products of around 160 companies.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://wikileaks.org/the-spyfiles.html |title=The Spyfiles |publisher=[[WikiLeaks]] |accessdate=21 December 2012 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Greenberg|first1=Andy|title=WikiLeaks Unveils 160 Firms' Surveillance Gear Sales Docs, Still No Submissions System|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/andygreenberg/2011/12/01/wikileaks-unveils-160-firms-surveillance-gear-sales-docs-still-no-submission-system/|publisher=Forbes|accessdate=31 May 2015}}</ref>
