{{member|name="Stalking Wolf"|nota=Reportedly, a great [[Apache]] [[Traditional Apache scout|scout]], master of wilderness living, nature [[mysticism|mystic]], and healer. After his parents and grandparents were [[Apache Wars|massacred]] by the US Army, he was raised by his great-grandfather "Coyote Thunder" who gave him the missions to save the remnants of their [[Lipan Apache people|tribe]] from annihilation, and to seek the common truth in various [[comparative religion|religions]]. He traveled on foot through the Americas for 63 years, mastering living in desert, forest, jungle, snow, and human settlements, ever expanding and deepening his knowledge, skill, awareness, and understanding of nature, human nature, religion, and spirituality. He learned meditation from a Chinese immigrant, and mentored [[Tom Brown (naturalist)|Tom Brown]].<ref>The life and teachings of Tom Brown's mentor "Stalking Wolf" and of Vladimir Megre's lover "Anastasia" are profoundly inspiring, but the physical existence of each of these two characters has been questioned due to insufficient evidence and corroboration.</ref>|ref=<ref>The most extended narrative of Stalking Wolf's life is Brown, Tom, ''Grandfather'', New York: [[Berkley Books|Berkley]], {{ISBN|0-425-18174-X}}.</ref><ref>The narrative of Stalking Wolf's spiritual exploration is Brown, Tom, ''Awakening Spirits'', New York: Berkley, {{ISBN|0-425-14140-3}}.</ref><ref>Brown, Tom, ''Conversations with Grandfather''.</ref>}}
