{{Infobox University |image_name= Harkness Tower Canopy Highsmith.jpg |image_size = |caption = |name = Yale OpenYaleCourses |latin_name = |native_name = |motto = |type = |president = |provost = |city = |state = |country = U.S. / online internationally |endowment = |staff = |faculty = |students = |undergrad = |postgrad = |colors = |mascot = |athletics = |nickname = |free_label = |free = |website = {{Official website}} |logo = }} '''Open Yale Courses''' is a project of [[Yale University]] to share full video and course materials from its [[undergraduate]] courses.
Open Yale Courses provides free access to a selection of introductory courses, and uses a [[Creative Commons licenses|Creative Commons]] Attribution-Noncommercial-[[Share Alike]] license.
Open Yale Courses launched in December 2007 with seven courses from various departments. The project now includes 42 courses from a broad range of introductory courses taught at Yale college.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://oyc.yale.edu/about#q13 |title=About Open Yale Courses (#13) |accessdate=2008-11-02 |work= |publisher=Yale.edu |date= }}</ref> The initiative was funded by the [[William and Flora Hewlett Foundation]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://oyc.yale.edu/about#q12 |title=About Open Yale Courses (#12) |accessdate=2008-11-02|work= |publisher=Yale.edu |date= }}</ref> which has supported other universities' [[OpenCourseWare]] projects.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://oyc.yale.edu/about#q15 |title=About Open Yale Courses (#15) |accessdate=2008-11-02 |work= |publisher=Yale.edu |date= }}</ref> As of August 2014 some of Yale's Open Courses are delivered by the European MooC platform [[Eliademy]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://eliademy.com/catalog/catalogsearch/result/index/?p=1&q=yale|title=Search results for: 'yale' |publisher=Eliademy |accessdate=29 April 2018}}</ref>
