{{notability|Biographies|date=September 2016}} {{Orphan|date=June 2016}}
'''Oyindamola Fakeye''' is a Nigerian creative producer currently working with VAN Lagos. She trained as a curator at [[Centre for Contemporary Art, Lagos]].<ref>http://curatorsintl.org/collaborators/oyinda_fakeye</ref>
==Life== She graduated from [[University of Nottingham]].<ref>http://www.visibleproject.org/blog/award/award-2015/jude-anogwih-oyindamola-fakeye-emeka-ogboh/</ref> With [[Emeka Ogboh]] and Jude Anogwih, she founded and directs Video Art Network, in [[Lagos]].<ref>http://futurecapetown.com/2015/04/future-lagos-voices-of-the-city-oyindamola-fakeye/#.VrY6Tk-FOUk</ref>
==Workshops== * ‘Party Games’ 2014 <ref>http://www.thenicheng.com/watch-yourself-a-spectacle-dedicated-to-self/</ref> * David Dale Gallery, Glasgow 2014 <ref>http://www.daviddalegallery.co.uk/programme/international-artist-initiated/</ref> * WHO IS WEARING MY T-SHIRT, Lagos, 2010 <ref>http://www.zohraopoku.com/index.php/who-is-wearing-my-t-shirt-workshop.html</ref><ref>http://www.ccalagos.org/archive/2010-pret-a-partager</ref>
